06/05/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase reportedly has proposed that the leadership of the ruling Social Democratic Party discuss possible cabinet shuffles.
The Romanian daily <I>Adevarul</I> quoted unnamed government sources Monday (5 May) who said that the number of ministries might be reduced from 27 to 15.
The ruling party will reportedly make a final decision at a national summit in the middle of the year.
(Adevarul, Rompres - 06/05/03)
